  "prompt": "How does the law define illegal money laundering activities?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions or legitimate businesses. Key elements typically include:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source of funds through multiple transactions\n3. Integration: Reintroducing the money into the economy as seemingly legitimate funds\n\nSpecific legal definitions can vary by jurisdiction, but most involve intentionally disguising the origins of criminally derived money.",
